OL,3,GNorth East
OL,4,
OL,5,CToday:FA few drier intervals to start,
OL,6,Fbut otherwise a largely wet and windy.
OL,7,FRain turning persistent, with a band
OL,8,Fof very heavy rain and strong gusts
OL,9,Fmoving south, clearing through the
OL,10,Fafternoon. Some brighter, but colder
OL,11,Fspells follow.
OL,12,
OL,13,CTonight:FWinds easing a little, but
OL,14,Fstaying brisk. Turning cold with clear
OL,15,Fspells and wintry showers, perhaps
OL,16,Fsome snow over hills. Some icy and
OL,17,Ffrost patches possible by dawn.
OL,23,QppppppppppppppppppppGSource: Met Office
OL,24,ANext Page  BWeather  CReg News  FReg TV
